The course will equip PhD students with a broad set of skills for both academic and industrial careers. The centre of the course will be developing a collaborative project among course participants (in groups) and learning all project management stages through the process. Other complementary exercises will also support the learning outcomes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course aims to equip PhD students with essential transferable skills that are critical for success after defence in both academia and industry. Students will learn effective project management, communication, leadership, and networking strategies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Doctoral student who completed the course: -can prepare a project budget and work plan -understands how project management takes place in the academic world -knows the feedback and basic principles of project proposals -can explain themselves understandably on their research topic -holds knowledge on group work dynamics and networking strategies
